ant staff\\\",\\\"Travel insurance\\\",\\\"Drinks other than those mentioned in the program\\\",\\\"Optional activities (e.g., River surfers in English Garden)\\\",\\\"Extra food & drinks beyond those specified\\\"]\"','[\"1\",\"3\",\"9\",\"15\",\"19\",\"23\",\"27\"]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-09-15 13:47:50','2025-09-17 10:38:43'),(25,25,'en','Agios Nikolaos, Elounda and cruise to Spinalonga','<p><strong>Highlights (What you&rsquo;ll love!)<br></strong>Cruise on the sparkling Mirabello Bay to the historic Spinalonga Island&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;Explore the Venetian fortress and learn its fascinating past <br>&nbsp; Stroll through the authentic fishing village of Elounda <br>&nbsp; &nbsp;Visit a Cretan olive oil farm and taste local products <br>&nbsp; &nbsp; Enjoy the charm of Agios Nikolaos &ndash; its lake, harbor &amp; cafes <br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Relax and soak in Crete&rsquo;s sun, sea, and stories</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy a day full of history and stunning scenery on our tour to the eastern part of the island, where we will embark on a cruise in the saltiest water here. You will explore the ruins of the Venetian fortress of Spinalonga and experience activities and attractions that reflect the authenticity and local charm of the fishing village of Elounda.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Then the journey will take you to a traditional olive oil farm and at the end of the day our tour will make a stop in Agios Nikolaos, a picturesque town on the northeast coast of Crete, a popular tourist destination with gorgeous scenery, a lively harbor and a relaxing atmosphere.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Lunch is included, transport and an experienced guide, so that your experience here is carefree and relaxing.<br><br></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Useful information</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&bull; The tour runs: <strong>Monday &amp; Thursday</strong> (The day of the tour may be changed, for operational reasons)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&bull;&nbsp;Estimated schedule: <strong>morning departure &ndash; afternoon return</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&bull;&nbsp;<strong>Lunch </strong>is<strong> included</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&bull;&nbsp;Additional cost:&nbsp;Entrance to Spinalonga (paid locally)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&bull;&nbsp;What to bring: swimsuit, sunscreen, camera</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&bull;&nbsp;The tour schedule may be subject to change or cancellation depending on weather conditions or the minimum number of people being reached</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<h5><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-ebee9161-7fff-2d75-2291-247bc26fdbe1\">Embark on a visit to Agios Nikolaos, Elounda the fishing village and Spinalonga Island Cruise and discover the true beauty of Crete</strong></h5>','Agios Nikolaos, Elounda & Spinalonga Cruise – History, Relaxation & Cretan Charm','<p>Discover Crete&rsquo;s eastern treasures on a guided day tour: cruise from Elounda to Spinalonga Island, visit the Venetian fortress, taste olive oil at a local farm, and enjoy the seaside beauty of Agios Nikolaos. Lunch and transport included.</p>','Spinalonga cruise, Elounda day trip, Agios Nikolaos tour, Crete boat trip, Spinalonga island fortress, Mirabello Bay cruise, Crete olive oil experience, Crete full day tour, Elounda Spinalonga Agios Nikolaos','\"[\\\"Visit to Selinari Monastery\\\",\\\"Elounda \\\\u2013 a glimpse into the simple life of an authentic fishing village\\\",\\\"Cruise to Spinalonga, an island full of history: from Venetian rule to leper colony\\\",\\\"Visit to a traditional olive oil farm\\\",\\\"Visit to the town\\\"]\"','\"[\\\"Entrance to Spinalonga (paid locally)\\\",\\\"Personal expenses & souvenirs\\\",\\\"Drinks during lunch\\\",\\\"Tips for guide and driver\\\"]\"','[\"1\",\"17\"]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-10-09 13:41:45','2025-10-09 14:12:25'),(27,27,'en','Rethymno, Spili & Matala','<p data-start=\"368\" data-end=\"685\">Discover the authentic side of Crete in a full-day tour through its traditional villages and historic towns. Visit Rethymno with its Venetian charm, stroll through the picturesque mountain village of Spili, and unwind in Matala &ndash; famous for its stunning beach, caves, and relaxed atmosphere.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"687\" data-end=\"879\"><strong data-start=\"687\" data-end=\"701\">Tour Type:</strong> One-Day Tour (Full Day &ndash; 8&ndash;9 hours)<br data-start=\"737\" data-end=\"740\"><strong data-start=\"740\" data-end=\"760\">Experience Type:</strong> Culture &amp; History, Sightseeing, Nature, Famous Beach<br data-start=\"791\" data-end=\"794\"><strong data-start=\"794\" data-end=\"811\">Audience Fit:</strong> Family-Friendly, Couples, Groups, Solo Travelers, Senior-Friendly</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"881\" data-end=\"1255\"><strong data-start=\"881\" data-end=\"914\"> Benefits (Why Book This Tour)&nbsp;</strong><br><br data-start=\"914\" data-end=\"917\"><strong>Guided Tour </strong>&ndash; Professional, licensed local guides<br data-start=\"966\" data-end=\"969\"><strong>Transfer Included </strong>&ndash; Comfortable round-trip from your hotel<br data-start=\"1027\" data-end=\"1030\"><strong>Free Cancellation</strong> &ndash; Book with confidence<br data-start=\"1070\" data-end=\"1073\"><strong>Book Now, Pay Later </strong>&ndash; Flexible reservation option<br data-start=\"1122\" data-end=\"1125\"><strong>Authentic Experience</strong> &ndash; Discover real Cretan traditions and history<br data-start=\"1191\" data-end=\"1194\"><strong>All-Day Comfort </strong>&ndash; Air-conditioned coach and expert guidance</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1257\" data-end=\"1651\"><strong data-start=\"1257\" data-end=\"1291\">Highlights (What you&rsquo;ll love!)</strong><br data-start=\"1291\" data-end=\"1294\">Explore the <strong>Old Town of Rethymno</strong> with its Venetian &amp; Ottoman landmarks<br data-start=\"1364\" data-end=\"1367\">Discover <strong>Spili &ndash; a traditional mountain village</strong> with cobblestone streets and lion-head fountains<br data-start=\"1463\" data-end=\"1466\">Relax in <strong>Matala,</strong> famous for its beach caves and bohemian vibe<br data-start=\"1527\" data-end=\"1530\">Enjoy <strong>local food, coffee, or shopping</strong> at seaside tavernas<br data-start=\"1587\" data-end=\"1590\">Experience <strong>a perfect mix of culture, nature, and relaxation</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1653\" data-end=\"1945\"><strong data-start=\"1653\" data-end=\"1672\">Is It Worth It?</strong><br data-start=\"1672\" data-end=\"1675\">Absolutely! This tour offers a perfect blend of Cretan culture, history, and coastal beauty. You&rsquo;ll explore the island&rsquo;s Venetian heritage, mountain charm, and relaxed seaside lifestyle &mdash; all in one full day, guided by local experts and without the stress of planning.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1947\" data-end=\"2711\"><strong data-start=\"1947\" data-end=\"1962\">Description</strong><br data-start=\"1962\" data-end=\"1965\">Your day begins with a scenic drive through Crete&rsquo;s landscapes toward <strong data-start=\"2035\" data-end=\"2047\">Rethymno</strong>, a charming port city blending Venetian, Ottoman, and Greek influences. Stroll through the Old Town, see the Venetian Loggia and Sultan Ibrahim Mosque, and admire the colorful facades of centuries-old houses.<br data-start=\"2256\" data-end=\"2259\">Next, head to <strong data-start=\"2273\" data-end=\"2282\">Spili</strong>, a picturesque mountain village known for its 25 lion-head fountains, traditional caf&eacute;s, and authentic local crafts. Continue the journey south to <strong data-start=\"2430\" data-end=\"2440\">Matala</strong>, one of Crete&rsquo;s most famous coastal villages, where natural caves in the cliffs overlook a golden sandy beach.<br data-start=\"2551\" data-end=\"2554\">Here you can swim, relax, or enjoy lunch at a seaside taverna before returning to your hotel, enriched with the flavors, sights, and stories of real Crete.</p>\r\n<p><strong>STANDARD RATES/PRICES:<br></strong> For hotels located in: Fodele; Bali; - Adults: