g> at seaside tavernas<br data-start=\"1587\" data-end=\"1590\">Experience <strong>a perfect mix of culture, nature, and relaxation</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1653\" data-end=\"1945\"><strong data-start=\"1653\" data-end=\"1672\">Is It Worth It?</strong><br data-start=\"1672\" data-end=\"1675\">Absolutely! This tour offers a perfect blend of Cretan culture, history, and coastal beauty. You&rsquo;ll explore the island&rsquo;s Venetian heritage, mountain charm, and relaxed seaside lifestyle &mdash; all in one full day, guided by local experts and without the stress of planning.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1947\" data-end=\"2711\"><strong data-start=\"1947\" data-end=\"1962\">Description</strong><br data-start=\"1962\" data-end=\"1965\">Your day begins with a scenic drive through Crete&rsquo;s landscapes toward <strong data-start=\"2035\" data-end=\"2047\">Rethymno</strong>, a charming port city blending Venetian, Ottoman, and Greek influences. Stroll through the Old Town, see the Venetian Loggia and Sultan Ibrahim Mosque, and admire the colorful facades of centuries-old houses.<br data-start=\"2256\" data-end=\"2259\">Next, head to <strong data-start=\"2273\" data-end=\"2282\">Spili</strong>, a picturesque mountain village known for its 25 lion-head fountains, traditional caf&eacute;s, and authentic local crafts. Continue the journey south to <strong data-start=\"2430\" data-end=\"2440\">Matala</strong>, one of Crete&rsquo;s most famous coastal villages, where natural caves in the cliffs overlook a golden sandy beach.<br data-start=\"2551\" data-end=\"2554\">Here you can swim, relax, or enjoy lunch at a seaside taverna before returning to your hotel, enriched with the flavors, sights, and stories of real Crete.</p>\r\n<p><strong>STANDARD RATES/PRICES:<br></strong> For hotels located in: Fodele; Bali; - Adults: &euro;65 / Children 2-12 years: &euro;32.5 (50% of Adult price!)&nbsp;<br> For hotels located in: Agia Pelagia; Lygaria; Ammoudara; Heraklion; Hersonissos; Kokk