itional villages, Matala caves, Spili fountains, Crete excursions from Heraklion','\"[\\\"Round-trip transportation from designated pick-up points\\\",\\\"Professional licensed guide\\\",\\\"Visit to Rethymno \\\\u2013 Venetian Loggia, Sultan Ibrahim Mosque, Old Town stroll\\\",\\\"Stop in Spili village \\\\u2013 traditional Cretan village with cobbled streets and whitewashed houses\\\",\\\"Free time in Matala \\\\u2013 famous for its caves, beach & seaside tavernas\\\"]\"','\"[\\\"Meals and drinks (lunch not included)\\\",\\\"Personal expenses & souvenirs\\\",\\\"Tips for guide and driver\\\"]\"','[\"1\",\"17\",\"31\",\"33\"]','','','','','2026-02-15 01:37:20','2026-02-15 01:37:20'),(63,28,'pl','Pamukkale i Hierapolis – Bawełniany Zamek Turcji','<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Tour Type:</strong> One-Day Tour (Full Day &ndash; 8&ndash;9 hours)<br><strong>Experience</strong> <strong>Type</strong>: Culture &amp; History, Sightseeing <br><strong>Audience Fit:</strong> Family-Friendly, Couples, Groups, Solo Travelers, Senior-Friendly</p>\r\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\">Benefits (Why Book This Tour)</h4>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Guided Tour</strong> &ndash; Professional, licensed local guides<br><strong>Transfer Included</strong> &ndash; Comfortable round-trip from your hotel<br><strong>Lunch Included</strong> &ndash; Authentic Turkish meal<br><strong>Free Cancellation</strong> &ndash; Book with confidence<br><strong>Book Now, Pay Later</strong> &ndash; Flexible reservation option<br><strong>Multilingual Experience</strong> &ndash; multilingual-speaking escort guide</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><br>Highlights (What you&rsquo;ll love!)</h3>\r\n<p>Walk barefoot on the world-famous&nbsp;<strong>white terraces of Pamukkal</strong>e, known as the &ldquo;Cotton Castle&rdquo;<br>Explore the&nbsp;<strong>ancient city of Hierapolis</strong> &ndash; a UNESCO World Heritage site<br>Take a dip in <strong>Cleopatra&rsquo;s thermal pool</strong> (optional)<br>Discover local crafts &ndash; <strong>handmade onyx and textile artistry</strong><br>Learn about <strong>Turkey&rsquo;s geological and cultural treasures</strong> from expert guides<br>Enjoy <strong>Turkish hospitality and cuisine</strong><br><strong><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-96904fc5-7fff-191d-5555-844e85b665ad\"></strong></strong> Experience <strong>a perfect blend of nature, history, and relaxation</strong></p>\r\n<h3 data-start=\"1654\" data-end=\"1679\">Is It Worth It?</h3>\r\n<p data-start=\"1680\" data-end=\"1968\">Absolutely! Pamukkale is one of the most photogenic and spiritually uplifting sites in Turkey &mdash; a true natural wonder paired with deep history. This full-day guided experience gives you the comfort of organized transport, expert storytelling, and local authenticity, without any stress.</p>\r\n<h3 data-start=\"1975\" data-end=\"1996\">Description</h3>\r\n<p data-start=\"1997\" data-end=\"2856\">Pamukkale, known as the &ldquo;Cotton Castle&rdquo;, is a natural masterpiece of white calcium terraces formed by thermal springs. Next to it lies <strong data-start=\"2134\" data-end=\"2148\">Hierapolis</strong>, an ancient Greco-Roman spa city once famed for its healing waters.<br data-start=\"2216\" data-end=\"2219\">Your journey begins with hotel pick-up and a scenic drive through the Turkish countryside. Upon arrival, your guide will lead you through the ancient ruins of Hierapolis, revealing temples, baths, and an ancient theater.<br data-start=\"2439\" data-end=\"2442\">You&rsquo;ll then walk barefoot on the bright white terraces of Pamukkale and can take an optional dip in Cleopatra&rsquo;s Pool - a warm, mineral-rich bath where history and legend intertwine.<br data-start=\"2623\" data-end=\"2626\">The day continues with visits to <strong data-start=\"2659\" data-end=\"2695\">local onyx and textile workshops</strong>, where artisans preserve centuries-old traditions. Lunch is included at a local restaurant before returning to your hotel, filled with unforgettable memories.</p>\r\n<h3 dir=