ast to the <strong data-start=\"2331\" data-end=\"2356\">ancient Lycian region</strong>.<br data-start=\"2357\" data-end=\"2360\">Your first stop is the <strong data-start=\"2383\" data-end=\"2411\">Church of Saint Nicholas</strong> in Demre &mdash; the resting place of the real Saint Nicholas, the inspiration for Santa Claus. This church, built in the Byzantine era, became one of Christianity&rsquo;s most important pilgrimage sites.<br data-start=\"2604\" data-end=\"2607\">Next, visit the <strong data-start=\"2623\" data-end=\"2647\">ancient city of Myra</strong>, renowned for its <strong data-start=\"2666\" data-end=\"2696\">spectacular rock-cut tombs</strong> carved high into the cliffs and its well-preserved <strong data-start=\"2748\" data-end=\"2765\">Roman theater</strong>. Here, you&rsquo;ll learn about the Lycian civilization and its unique architectural style.<br data-start=\"2851\" data-end=\"2854\">After lunch, continue to <strong data-start=\"2879\" data-end=\"2889\">Kekova</strong>, where you&rsquo;ll embark on a <strong data-start=\"2916\" data-end=\"2937\">short boat cruise</strong> over the <strong data-start=\"2947\" data-end=\"2962\">sunken city</strong>, partly submerged due to ancient earthquakes. From the glass-bottom boat, you&rsquo;ll see <strong data-start=\"3048\" data-end=\"3104\">ruins of homes, staircases, and ancient harbor walls</strong> beneath the sea &mdash; an extraordinary sight combining history and nature.<br data-start=\"3175\" data-end=\"3178\">The day ends with a relaxing drive back to your hotel, filled with remarkable memories of Turkey&rsquo;s ancient past.</p>\r\n<hr data-start=\"3407\" data-end=\"3410\">\r\n<h3 data-start=\"3412\" data-end=\"3440\"><strong data-start=\"3416\" data-end=\"3438\">Useful Information</strong></h3>\r\n<p data-start=\"3441\" data-end=\"3597\"><strong data-start=\"3441\" data-end=\"3454\">Tour Day:</strong> Every Tuesday<br data-start=\"3468\" data-end=\"3471\"><strong data-start=\"3471\" data-e