rong data-start=\"2208\" data-end=\"2233\">Bardo National Museum</strong>, home to one of the <strong data-start=\"2254\" data-end=\"2303\">largest Roman mosaic collections in the world</strong>. As you walk through its galleries, you will discover breathtaking mosaics, ancient sculptures, and rare artifacts that trace Tunisia&rsquo;s rich past. Your journey continues to <strong data-start=\"2477\" data-end=\"2489\">Carthage</strong>, the legendary Phoenician and Roman city once ruled by Hannibal. Explore its impressive ruins, Punic ports, and ancient temples that reveal the rise and fall of one of the most influential civilizations in Mediterranean history. The tour then takes you to <strong data-start=\"2746\" data-end=\"2763\">Sidi Bou Said</strong>, Tunisia&rsquo;s iconic hilltop village painted entirely in <strong data-start=\"2818\" data-end=\"2836\">blue and white</strong>. With stunning sea views, charming caf&eacute;s, and narrow cobbled streets, it is one of the most picturesque places in North Africa &mdash; perfect for photos, slow exploration, and a moment of pure Mediterranean calm. Finally, enjoy a panoramic tour of <strong data-start=\"3080\" data-end=\"3089\">Tunis</strong>, including its historic <strong data-start=\"3114\" data-end=\"3138\">UNESCO-listed Medina</strong>, a vibrant maze of markets, traditional craftsmen, and centuries-old monuments that capture the soul of the capital. With a guided itinerary, transfers, entrance fees, and lunch included, this tour invites you to experience Tunisia&rsquo;s cultural treasures in the most comfortable and enriching way.</p>\r\n<hr data-start=\"3436\" data-end=\"3439\">\r\n<h3 data-start=\"3441\" data-end=\"3458\"><strong data-start=\"3444\" data-end=\"3456\">Subtitle</strong></h3>\r\n<p data-start=\"3459\" data-end=\"3557\">A full-day cultural journey through Tunisia&rsquo;s most iconic historical and Mediterranean highlights.</p>\r\n<hr data-start=\"3559\" data-end=\"3562\">\r\n<h3 data-start=\"3564\