What You&rsquo;ll Love!)</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Visit<strong> Kairouan</strong>, one of Islam&rsquo;s holiest cities (UNESCO)<br>Explore the <strong>Great Mosque of Kairouan</strong>, a masterpiece of Islamic architecture<br>Discover<strong> Matmata,</strong> famous for its underground Berber cave homes<br>See the r<strong>eal Star Wars film locations</strong><br>Cross the desert in a <strong>4x4 off-road adventure</strong><br>Witness sunrise at <strong>Chott El Jerid,</strong> Tunisia&rsquo;s legendary salt lake<br>Visit <strong>El Jem Roman Amphitheatre (UNESCO)</strong><br>Stay <strong>overnight in a desert hotel, with dinner &amp; breakfast included</strong></p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Is It Worth It?</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Yes ! This is the signature adventure of Tunisia. A journey deep into the Sahara, rich with culture, history, and dramatic scenery. It&rsquo;s the most complete way to experience Tunisia beyond the coastline, ideal for travelers seeking both comfort and real adventure.</p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Description</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This immersive 2-day Sahara journey begins with a visit to<strong> Kairouan,</strong> one of the most important spiritual centers of Islam and a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Explore its ancient medina, the impressive Great Mosque of Kairouan, and the legendary Bir Barouta well. Continue toward southern Tunisia where you&rsquo;ll arrive in Matmata, home to the region&rsquo;s traditional Berber cave dwellings, some of which were featured in Star Wars. You&rsquo;ll step inside these underground houses and learn how Berber families still live in harmony with the desert. The adventure continues with a thrilling 4&times;4 off-road ride across dramatic desert terrain, including mountains, dunes, and remote villages. The day ends with dinner and an overnight stay in a desert hotel. Early the next morning, experience the unforgettable sunrise over Chott El Jerid, a vast salt lake known 