 on a cruise in the saltiest water here. You will explore the ruins of the Venetian fortress of Spinalonga and experience activities and attractions that reflect the authenticity and local charm of the fishing village of Elounda.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Then the journey will take you to a traditional olive oil farm and at the end of the day our tour will make a stop in Agios Nikolaos, a picturesque town on the northeast coast of Crete, a popular tourist destination with gorgeous scenery, a lively harbor and a relaxing atmosphere.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Lunch is included, transport and an experienced guide, so that your experience here is carefree and relaxing.<br><br></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Useful information</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&bull; The tour runs: <strong>Monday &amp; Thursday</strong> (The day of the tour may be changed, for operational reasons)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&bull;&nbsp;Estimated schedule: <strong>morning departure &ndash; afternoon return</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&bull;&nbsp;<strong>Lunch </strong>is<strong> included</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&bull;&nbsp;Additional cost:&nbsp;Entrance to Spinalonga (paid locally)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&bull;&nbsp;What to bring: swimsuit, sunscreen, camera</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&bull;&nbsp;The tour schedule may be subject to change or cancellation depending on weather conditions or the minimum number of people being reached</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<h5><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-ebee9161-7fff-2d75-2291-247bc26fdbe1\">Embark on a visit to Agios Nikolaos, Elounda the fishing village and Spinalonga Island Cruise and discover the true beauty of Crete</strong></h5>','agios-nikolaos-elounda-and-cruise-to-spinalonga','Central Eastern Crete',NULL,NULL,11,12,NULL,43.00,34.00,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'\"[\\\"Visit to Selinari Monastery\\\",\\\"Elounda \\\\u2013 a glimpse into the simple life of an authentic fishing village\\\",\\\"Cruise to Spinalonga, an island full of history: from Venetian rule to leper colony\\\",\\\"Visit to a traditional olive oil farm\\\",\\\"Visit to the town\\\"]\"','\"[\\\"Entrance to Spinalonga (paid locally)\\\",\\\"Personal expenses & souvenirs\\\",\\\"Drinks during lunch\\\",\\\"Tips for guide and driver\\\"]\"','8-9 h','No restrictions','[\"English\"]','Mobile voucher or printed tiket','[\"1\",\"17\"]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-10-09 13:41:45','2025-10-10 07:25:07',1,1,1,0,'{\"infant\":{\"enabled\":true,\"count\":3,\"price\":0,\"min_age\":1,\"max_age\":2},\"baby\":{\"enabled\":false,\"count\":0,\"price\":null,\"min_age\":null,\"max_age\":null},\"child\":{\"enabled\":true,\"count\":10,\"price\":10,\"min_age\":5,\"max_age\":17},\"adult\":{\"enabled\":true,\"count\":10,\"price\":20,\"min_age\":18,\"max_age\":99}}','Agios Nikolaos, Elounda & Spinalonga Cruise – History, relaxation and dreamlike landscapes',NULL,NULL,1),(27,'Rethymno, Spili & Matala','<p data-start=\"368\" data-end=\"685\">Discover the authentic side of Crete in a full-day tour through its traditional villages and historic towns. Visit Rethymno with its Venetian charm, stroll through the picturesque mountain village of Spili, and unwind in Matala &ndash; famous for its stunning beach, caves, and relaxed atmosphere.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"687\" data-end=\"879\"><strong data-start=\"687\" data-end=\"701\">Tour Type:</strong> One-Day Tour (Full Day &ndash; 8&ndash;9 hours)<br data-start=\"737\" data-end=\"740\"><strong data-start=\"740\" data-end=\"760\">Experience Type:</strong> Culture &amp; History, Sightseeing, Nature, Famous Beach<br data-start=\"791\" data-end=\"794\"><strong data-start=\"794\" data-end=\"811\">Audience Fit:</strong> Family-Friendly, Couples, Groups, Solo Travelers, Senior-Friendly</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"881\" data-end=\"1255\"><strong data-start=\"881\" data-end=\"914\"> Benefits (Why Book This Tour)&nbsp;</strong><br><br data-start=\"914\" data-end=\"917\"><strong>Guided Tour </strong>&ndash; Professional, licensed local guides<br data-start=\"966\" data-end=\"969\"><strong>Transfer Included </strong>&ndash; Comfortable round-trip from your hotel<br data-start=\"1027\" data-end=\"1030\"><strong>Free Cancellation</strong> &ndash; Book with confidence<br data-start=\"1070\" data-end=\"1073\"><strong>Book Now, Pay Later </strong>&ndash; Flexible reservation option<br data-start=\"1122\" data-end=\"1125\"><strong>Authentic Experience</strong> &ndash; Discover real Cretan traditions and history<br data-start=\"1191\" data-end=\"1194\"><strong>All-Day Comfort </strong>&ndash; Air-conditioned coach and expert guidance</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1257\" data-end=\"1651\"><strong data-start=\"1257\" data-end=\"1291\">Highlights (What you&rsquo;ll love!)</strong><br data-start=\"1291\" data-end=\"1294\">Explore the <strong>Old Town of Rethymno</strong> with its Venetian &amp; Ottoman landmarks<br data-start=\"1364\" data-end=\"1367\">Discover <strong>Spili &ndash; a traditional mountain village</strong> with cobblestone streets and lion-head fountains<br data-start=\"1463\" data-end=\"1466\">Relax in <strong>Matala,</strong> famous for its beach caves and bohemian vibe<br data-start=\"1527\" data-end=\"1530\">Enjoy <strong>local food, coffee, or shopping</strong> at seaside tavernas<br data-start=\"1587\" data-end=\"1590\">Experience <strong>a perfect mix of culture, nature, and relaxation</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1653\" data-end=\"1945\"><strong data-start=\"1653\" data-end=\"1672\">Is It Worth It?</strong><br data-start=\"1672\" data-end=\"1675\">Absolutely! This tour offers a perfect blend of Cretan culture, history, and coastal beauty. You&rsquo;ll explore the island&rsquo;s Venetian heritage, mountain charm, and relaxed seaside lifestyle &mdash; all in one full day, guided by local experts and without the stress of planning.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1947\" data-end=\"2711\"><strong data-start=\"1947\" data-end=\"1962\">Description</strong><br data-start=\"1962\" data-end=\"1965\">Your day begins with a scenic drive through Crete&rsquo;s landscapes toward <strong data-start=\"2035\" data-end=\"2047\">Rethymno</strong>, a charming port city blending Venetian, Ottoman, and Greek influences. Stroll through the Old Town, see the Venetian Loggia and Sultan Ibrahim Mosque, and admire the colorful facades of centuries-old houses.<br data-start=\"2256\" data-end=\"2259\">Next, head to <strong data-start=\"2273\" data-end=\"2282\">Spili</strong>, a picturesque mountain village known for its 25 lion-head fountains, traditional caf&eacute;s, and authentic local crafts. Continue the journey south to <strong data-start=\"2430\" data-end=\"2440\">Matala</strong>, one of Crete&rsquo;s most famous coastal villages, where natural caves in the cliffs overlook a golden sandy beach.<br data-start=\"2551\" data-end=\"2554\">Here you can swim, relax, or enjoy lunch at a seaside taverna before returning to your hotel, enriched with the flavors, sights, and stories of real Crete.</p>\r\n<p><strong>STANDARD RATES/PRICES:<br></strong> For hotels located in: Fodele; Bali; - Adults: &euro;65 / Children 2-12 years: &euro;32.5 (50% of Adult price!)&nbsp;<br> For hotels located in: Agia Pelagia; Lygaria; Ammoudara; Heraklion; Hersonissos; Kokkini Hani; Gournes; Gouves; Analipsi; Anissaras; Stalida; Malia; -&nbsp; Extra charge 5 euro for adult: Adults: &euro;70 / Children 2-12 years: &euro;35<br> For hotels located in: Agios Nikolaos; Ammoudara (Ag.Nikolaos); Elounda; Istron; Sissi; Vathi; -Extra charge 5 euro for adult: Adults: &euro;90 / Children 2-12 years: &euro;45<br> The excursion is NOT valid for hotels located in: Adelianos Kambos; Panormo; Pigianos Kampos (Rethymno); Platanias Rethymno; Rethymno; Sfakaki; Georgioupolis; Kavros.<br><br><strong>Useful Information:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tour Day</strong>: <strong>Wednesday </strong>(may change for operational reasons)<br><strong>Duration:</strong> Full-day tour (morning departure &ndash; evening return)<br><strong>What to bring</strong>: Swimsuit, sunscreen, camera, hat</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1;\"><strong>Keep your travel plans flexible</strong></p>\r\n<p>Free cancellation: Cancel up to 48 hours in advance for a full refund<br>Reserve now &amp; pay later: you can book your spot and pay nothing until 72 hours/(3 days before pickup.</p>\r\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-ea7b2b01-7fff-a1ee-0512-3e24327ef209\">Note: </strong>Tour may be adjusted or cancelled due to weather or minimum group size</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>Discover the authentic side of Crete in a full-day tour through its traditional villages and historic towns. Visit Rethymno with its Venetian charm, stroll through the picturesque mountain village of Spili, and unwind in Matala - famous for its stunning beach, caves, and relaxed atmosphere.</p>','rethymno-spili-matala','Central Eastern Crete',NULL,NULL,11,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'\"[\\\"Round-trip transportation from designated pick-up points\\\",\\\"Professional licensed guide\\\",\\\"Visit to Rethymno \\\\u2013 Venetian Loggia, Sultan Ibrahim Mosque, Old Town stroll\\\",\\\"Stop in Spili village \\\\u2013 traditional Cretan village with cobbled streets and whitewashed houses\\\",\\\"Free time in Matala \\\\u2013 famous for its caves, beach & seaside tavernas\\\"]\"','\"[\\\"Meals and drinks (lunch not included)\\\",\\\"Personal expenses & souvenirs\\\",\\\"Tips for guide and driver\\\"]\"','8-9 h','No restrictions','[\"English\"]','Mobile voucher or printed tiket','[\"1\",\"17\",\"31\",\"33\"]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,1,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-10-10 14:24:53','2025-10-15 11:19:09',1,1,1,0,'{\"infant\":{\"enabled\":true,\"count\":0,\"price\":0,\"min_age\":0,\"max_age\":1},\"baby\":{\"enabled\":false,\"count\":0,\"price\":null,\"min_age\":null,\"max_age\":null},\"child\":{\"enabled\":true,\"count\":0,\"price\":32.5,\"min_age\":2,\"max_age\":11},\"adult\":{\"enabled\":true,\"count\":18,\"price\":6