INSERT INTO `term_and_conditions` VALUES (1,'en','<h1 dir=\"ltr\">MementoTrip(s) - General Terms and Conditions</h1>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">1. About Us</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">MementoTrips (referred to as &ldquo;MementoTrips,&rdquo; &ldquo;MementoTrip&rdquo; <a href=\"http://mementotrip.com\">MementoTrip.com</a>, &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us&rdquo; or &ldquo;our&rdquo;) operates an online platform and the related mobile applications (the &ldquo;Platform&rdquo;) through which independent tourism suppliers, local providers, tour operators, destination management companies, local travel services providers (&ldquo;Providers&rdquo;) can market and promote tours, activities, excursions, experiences and other travel‐related services (&ldquo;Activities&rdquo;) to customers, travellers (&ldquo;User&rdquo; or &ldquo;Users&rdquo; or &ldquo;you&rdquo;). <br>MementoTrips acts as an intermediary or commercial agent on behalf of Providers; it does not itself organize or operate any Activities. When you make a booking through MementoTrips, your contract for the Activity is concluded directly between you and the Provider, while MementoTrips brokers the transaction and collects payments on behalf of the Provider. <br><br>MementoTrips is not responsible for the performance of the Activities or for content supplied by Providers&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Contact Information</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Company name: MementoTrip s&nbsp; ( ce company opereaza details to be inserted)<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Head office: [address]<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Email: [info@mementotrip.com]<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Customer service phone: [phone number; available hours]<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">2. Definitions</h2>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Term</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Meaning</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Platform</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The website (<a href=\"http://www.mementotrips.com\">www.mementotrip.com</a> ) and associated mobile applications operated by MementoTrip (s)?!</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">User/Customer</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Any individual or legal entity with full legal capacity who visits, browses&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">the Platform and/or uses its functionalities to learn about or book, purchase Tours, Trips, Excursions, Experiences or Activities.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Provider/Supplier</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A third-party travel entrepreneur, travel company, or local service provider offering Activities through the Platform. Providers may be local DMC (Destination Management Company), tour operators, attraction owners, activity organizers or resellers, local entrepreneurs, local guides etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Activity/Experience</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Any tour, trip, excursion, Experience, Activity, ticket, sightseeing or other&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">tourism and or travel service listed to be booked and for sale through the Platform - organized at the destination by a Provider/Supplier</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Service Agreement</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The contract for an Activity that is concluded directly between a User and a Provider. MementoTrips acts only as an agent in concluding the Service Agreement&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Booking Price</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The total price payable by the User for an Activity, including the Provider&rsquo;s&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">price plus MementoTrips&rsquo; commission for brokering the Service Agreement</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Reseller</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Any authorized partner: company, or individual, who promotes, distributes, or sells Experiences listed on the Platform to end customers, under a&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">commercial or affiliate agreement, acting as an independent intermediary</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;and not as an agent or representative of Our Company Name.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">3. Scope and Acceptance of Terms</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">These General Terms and Conditions (&ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) govern your use of the Platform and all services provided by MementoTrip(s). By accessing or using any part of the Platform, you agree to be bound by these Terms. (as a User/Customer, Provider/Supplier, Reseller) If you do not accept the Terms, you must refrain from using the Platform.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">These Terms apply worldwide unless more specific terms apply to a particular jurisdiction or are required by local law. MementoTrips may issue additional regulations or policies for particular services or campaigns; those specific terms will prevail over these general provisions where they conflict.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">We may, at our sole discretion, amend these Terms from time to time. We will publish the amended version on the Platform and indicate the effective date. Continued use after amendments constitutes your acceptance.<br><br></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Additional terms may apply to specific Tours, Excursions , xperiences or Activities (e.g., Supplier cancellation policy) and such terms form part of the contract between you (User . Customer) and the Provider//Supplier</p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">4. Role of MementoTrip and Service Agreements</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Intermediary status - MementoTrips provides information about Activities and Experiences offered by independent Providers and facilitates the booking and conclusion of Service Agreements between Users and Providers. MementoTrips acts as a commercial agent on behalf of Providers. When you book an Activity or Experience, the contract is between you and the Provider; MementoTrips is not a party to the contract and is not responsible for the performance and for any part of the organizing and delivery of the activity and local experience.&nbsp;<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Booking process - To make a booking, you must select an Activity, provide the required information and a valid payment method. By completing the checkout process, you submit a binding offer to purchase the Activity from the Provider. The Provider (via MementoTrips) will send you a booking confirmation. You must review the confirmation carefully and notify us immediately of any errors. The provider will communicate with you and reconfirm the necessary details and the information necessary and specific for the local activity you booked using the platform.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Pricing and commission - The price displayed for an Activity includes MementoTrips&rsquo; commission charged to Providers for brokering the Service Agreement. Prices may vary due to currency exchange rates or additional fees charged by payment institutions. MementoTrips may offer promotional codes or refund vouchers, subject to separate conditions. The special discounts are communicated on the platform if and when available. <br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Service provider terms - Providers may require Users to accept their own terms and conditions (Supplier‑Customer T&amp;Cs). By booking an Activity, you agree to be bound by those specific terms. If there is a conflict between Provider terms and these General Terms, the provisions most favourable to you will prevail, unless mandatory law provides otherwise. Payment terms, cancellation, changes, and no‐show rules are subject to the Supplier&rsquo;s terms unless otherwise stated.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">We reserve the right to cancel or change the booking in case of unavailability, force majeure, or Supplier&rsquo;s failure to perform. We will notify you and propose an alternative or full refund.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">5. Payment and Fees</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Payment processing - MementoTrips collects the Booking Price on behalf of the Provider. You authorize MementoTrips to process your payment and to transfer funds to the Provider. Payment may be made through credit/debit cards, digital wallets or other methods offered at checkout.<br>Payment is made via the Platform through our payment provider. By placing a booking, you authorize the payment provider to charge the payment method.<br>In the event of payment failure or suspected fraud, we may cancel the booking or refuse service<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Currency and charges - Unless otherwise stated, prices are shown in the currency relevant to your locale. Banks or payment service providers may apply currency conversion fees or other charges, for which you are responsible.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">VAT and local taxes - Prices include applicable VAT or other sales taxes imposed by law. Some jurisdictions require that additional local taxes be paid upon arrival or at the event venue; these will be disclosed where known.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">6. Changes, Cancellations and Refunds</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Cancellation by User - Unless different conditions are specified in the Activity description or the Provider&rsquo;s T&amp;Cs, the following standard policy applies&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"2\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">More than 72 hours before the start of the Activity: full refund of the Booking Price.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"2\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Between 48 hours and 24 hours before the start of Activity: 50% refund.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"2\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Within 24 hours of the Activity start time or in case of no‑show: no refund.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Modifications - To change or cancel a booking, you must submit a request via email, using the platform, or other official contact details. Late requests may be denied. Some Activities may require you to present identification matching the name on your booking; failure to do so may be treated as a no‑show.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Provider‑specific conditions - For some Activities, Providers specify different cancellation deadlines (e.g., 48 hours or non‑refundable). Such conditions will be clearly stated on the Activity page or in the Provider&rsquo;s T&amp;Cs. You are responsible for reviewing those conditions before booking.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Refunds - Refunds are issued to the original payment method, unless you choose a MementoTrips refund voucher. Refund vouchers are non‑transferable, have an expiry date, and may be subject to additional usage conditions.<br>No refunds are given for &ldquo;no-shows&rdquo; unless otherwise stated.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Cancellation by Provider or Force Majeure - Providers may cancel or modify an Activity due to circumstances beyond their control (e.g., weather, safety, government restrictions). In such cases, MementoTrips will inform you and facilitate a refund or rescheduling according to the Provider&rsquo;s policy. MementoTrips is not liable for additional costs incurred by you due to such changes.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Right of withdrawal (EU Consumers) - Under the EU Consumer Rights Directive, consumers may withdraw from a distance contract within 14 days without giving a reason. However, this right does not apply to services related to leisure or activities with a specific date. If the Activity is supplied in full with your prior consent before the 14‑day period expires, you acknowledge that your right to withdraw is lost.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">7. Other&nbsp; Supplier Obligations &amp; Customer Obligations</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Suppliers warrant that the description of their Experience is accurate, that they have the necessary licences/permits, and will provide the Experience as described.<br><br></h2>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Customers must arrive at the agreed meeting point/time, comply with Supplier requirements, behave appropriately, and meet any age/health restrictions. Failure may result in forfeiture of service without refund.</h2>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">8. Liability and Disclaimer</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">No responsibility for Provider services - MementoTrips is not a tour operator. The Provider is solely responsible for performing the Activity and for any representations made about it. MementoTrips disclaims all liability for any injury, loss, damage, accident, delay or other irregularity arising out of or in connection with the services provided by the Provider.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Information accuracy - Activity descriptions, photos and customer reviews are provided by Providers or other Users. While MementoTrips endeavours to verify the information, it does not guarantee its 100% accuracy. Any reliance on such content is at your own acceptance.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Limitation of liability - To the maximum extent permitted by law, MementoTrips&rsquo; liability for claims arising under these Terms is limited to direct damages not exceeding the total Booking Price paid by you for the Activity in question. MementoTrips is not liable for indirect or consequential damages, lost profits, or punitive damages. Nothing in these Terms excludes liability for death or personal injury caused by negligence or for fraud.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Force majeure - MementoTrips is not liable for any failure to perform due to circumstances beyond its reasonable control, including natural disasters, strikes, war, pandemic, or technical problems affecting the Platform.<br><br></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">8. Intellectual Property</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">All materials, trademarks and logos displayed on the Platform (including text, photos, software and databases) are protected by copyright and related intellectual‑property rights. You may view and print materials for personal use only. You may not copy, reproduce, modify, distribute or create derivative works without express permission. User reviews remain the property of the author, but by posting them, you grant MementoTrips a non‑exclusive, worldwide, royalty‑free licence to use and display your content in connection with the Platform and its promotion.</p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">9. Modifications to the Terms</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">MementoTrips may modify these Terms for valid reasons, such as changes in law, expansion of services, or technical adjustments. Users will be notified by publication on the Platform and, where appropriate, by email. Continued use of the Platform after modifications come into effect constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms. If you do not accept the modifications, you may cancel your account and stop using the Platform.</p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">10. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">These Terms are governed by (?!Romanian law) or optionally [Poland or other applicable country])<br>Disputes that cannot be resolved amicably shall be submitted to the competent (?Romanian courts/Polish courts). <br>Consumers resident in the EU may also seek alternative dispute resolution via the European Online Dispute Resolution platform.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">11. Miscellaneous</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If any provision of these Terms is held invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions remain in force.<br>The waiver of any breach does not constitute waiver of future breaches.<br>These Terms constitute the entire agreement between you and us regarding your use of the Platform</p>\r\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-95229236-7fff-2923-60c4-c50fde16b09d\"><br><br></strong></p>',NULL,'2026-02-04 14:37:12'),(22,'pl','<h4>01.Introduction</h4>\r\n<p>A Privacy Policy is a legal document that informs users about the data collected, how it\'s used, and how it\'s protected. It typically includes information about the type of personal our ainformation collected (such as names, email addresses, etc.), the purpose of collection, and whether the information is shared with third parties. It outlines the rights of users regarding their data, such as the right to access, correct, or delete their information.</p>\r\n<h4>02. Educve Terms of Service</h4>\r\n<p>Terms of Service (also known as Terms and Conditions or Terms of Use) set the rules and guidelines for using a particular service or platform. They establish the contractual relationship between the user and the service provider. They often include details about user behavior, content usage policies, disclaimers, limitations of liability, and procedures for dispute resolution.Users typically agree to these terms by using the service.When you visit a website or use an online service, you are usually asked to agree to both the Privacy Policy and the Terms of Service. These documents are crucial for transparency, legal compliance, and establishing the terms under which users can access and use the service.</p>\r\n<p>It\'s important for businesses and service providers to keep these documents up-to-date and easily accessible to users. If you have specific questions or concerns about privacy policies or terms of service, feel free to provide more details, and I\'ll do my best to assist you.</p>\r\n<h4>3. Protect Your Property</h4>\r\n<p>Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry\'s standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown as printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book. It has survived not only five centuriezcs but also the on leap into as eylectronic typesetting, remaining as essentially unchanged. It wasn&rsquo;t popularised in the 1960s with the release of Letraszvxet sheets containing Lorem Ipsum our spassages, andei more recently with a desktop publishing software like Aldus PageMaker including versions of Lorem Ipsum to make a type specimen book. five centuries but also a the on leap into electronic typesetting, remaining essentially unchanged. It aswasn&rsquo;t popularised in the 1960s with the release of Letraset sheets containing Lorem Ipsum passages, andei more recently with desktop our aspublishing software like Aldus PageMaker 