um &rarr; El Jem Amphitheatre &rarr; Archaeology Museum &rarr; Return to Hotel</p>',NULL,'8-9 h',NULL,NULL,1,'2025-11-19 12:27:10','2025-11-19 12:27:10'),(71,46,'Pick up points and extra charges',1,'<p>Free pick up from Sousse, Monastir, Port El Kantaoui and Mahdia&nbsp;<br>extra charge: 6 euros&nbsp; for Pick up from Hammamet, Nabeul, Tunis. (the Northern resorts)&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'2025-11-19 12:31:06','2025-11-19 12:31:06'),(72,47,'Monastir & Sousse – Cultural Tour',1,'<p>Hotel Pickup &rarr; Monastir Ribat &rarr; Bourguiba Mausoleum &rarr; Sousse Medina (UNESCO) &rarr; Sousse Archaeological Museum &rarr; Sousse Ribat &rarr; Return to Hotel</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2025-11-19 13:07:26','2025-11-19 13:07:26'),(73,48,'Paradise Sea Luxury: Island Escape & Semi-Submarine Experience',1,'<p>Hotel Pickup &rarr; Marina &rarr; Semi-Submarine Experience &rarr; Boat to Paradise Island &rarr; Snorkeling Stop &rarr; Island Beach Time &rarr; Lunch &amp; Entertainment &rarr; Return Boat &rarr; Hotel Drop-Off</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2025-11-20 14:13:50','2025-11-20 14:13:50'),(74,49,'Eden Island - Luxury Beach Escape with Coral Reef Tour',1,'<p>Hotel Pickup &rarr; Port &rarr; Boat Ride to Eden Island &rarr; Coral Reef Tour &rarr; Island Beach Time &rarr; Buffet Lunch &rarr; Free Time &rarr; Return Boat &rarr; Hotel Drop-Off</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2025-11-20 14:38:55','2025-11-20 14:38:55'),(75,53,'Day 1 - Arrival in Prague',1,'<p>Your journey begins at your Departure Airport where you board the flight to Prague. <br>After landing, board the transfer bus and travel to the hotel.</p>\r\n<p>Optional, dinner and craft beer at the most famous Prague brewery. Accommodation in Prague at the Amedia Express Prague, Trademark Collection by Wyndham 3* hotel (or similar).</p>\r\n<p>Accommodation<br>Amedia Express Prague, Trademark Collection by Wyndham (or similar).</p>','PRAGUE','8-9 hours','optional Dinner','uploads/custom-images/itinerary-2025-12-19-05-31-28-2470.jfif',1,'2025-12-19 15:31:28','2025-12-19 15:31:28'),(76,53,'Day 2 – Prague: The City of a Hundred Spires',2,'<p data-start=\"1410\" data-end=\"1655\">Prague unfolds slowly, beautifully - a city where every street feels like a postcard. Often compared to Paris for its elegance, Prague has its own unmistakable soul, shaped by centuries of history, architecture, and everyday life lived outdoors.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1657\" data-end=\"2074\">The day begins at <strong data-start=\"1675\" data-end=\"1698\">St. Vitus Cathedral</strong>, one of the city&rsquo;s most powerful symbols. Rising above Prague Castle, the cathedral tells a 600-year story of devotion, craftsmanship, and ambition. From here, you continue through <strong data-start=\"1880\" data-end=\"1897\">Prague Castle</strong>, a fairytale-like complex officially recognized as the largest medieval castle in the world &mdash; a place that feels less like a monument and more like a living city within a city.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"2076\" data-end=\"2325\">Crossing the iconic <strong data-start=\"2096\" data-end=\"2114\">Charles Bridge</strong>, lined with statues and street musicians, you experience one of Prague&rsquo;s most romantic and atmospheric walks. Locals, travelers, and artists share the bridge, making it a place where the city truly comes alive.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"2327\" data-end=\"2564\">In <strong data-start=\"2330\" data-end=\"2349\">Old Town Square</strong>, time slows down. You admire the historic Town Hall and the famous <strong data-start=\"2417\" data-end=\"2439\">Astronomical Clock</strong>, whose hourly mechanical show still draws crowds &mdash; not because it is loud or spectacular, but because it is quietly magical.</p>\r\n<hr data-start=\"2566\" data-end=\"2569\">\r\n<h3 data-start=\"2571\" data-end=\"2598\"><strong data-start=\"2575\" data-end=\"2598\">Free Time &amp; Leisure</strong></h3>\r\n<p data-start=\"2600\" data-end=\"2941\">Prague is also about pleasure and curiosity. Even if beer isn&rsquo;t your thing, tasting it here is part of the experience. One playful option is <strong data-start=\"2741\" data-end=\"2771\">Vytopna Railway Restaurant</strong> in Wenceslas Square, where drinks arrive at your table by miniature trains running on nearly a kilometer of tracks - a place that mixes Czech beer culture with pure fun.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"2943\" data-end=\"3309\">The afternoon is yours to shape. Wander, shop, photograph, or simply sit at a caf&eacute; and watch the city pass by. <br><br>For an amazing different perspective, the evenenig <strong data-start=\"3110\" data-end=\"3133\">Vltava River cruise</strong> offers a peaceful way to see Prague from the water. Floating beneath Charles Bridge at dusk, with city lights slowly turning on, the city reveals a softer, more intimate side.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"3311\" data-end=\"3377\">Prague isn&rsquo;t just something you see - <strong data-start=\"3349\" data-end=\"3376\">it&rsquo;s something you feel</strong>.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"3379\" data-end=\"3533\">In the evening, you return to your hotel for a restful night.<br data-start=\"3440\" data-end=\"3443\"><strong data-start=\"3443\" data-end=\"3461\">Accommodation:</strong> Amedia Express Prague, Trademark Collection by Wyndham 3★ (or similar).</p>',NULL,NULL,'optional Lunch, optional Dinner on the included River Cruise','uploads/custom-images/itinerary-2025-12-19-06-27-04-2842.png',2,'2025-12-19 16:27:04','2025-12-19 16:27:04'),(77,53,'Day 3 – Prague at Your Own Rhythm',3,'<p data-start=\"199\" data-end=\"254\">Today is about slowing down and making Prague your own.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"256\" data-end=\"561\">With the city&rsquo;s iconic landmarks already behind you, you now have the freedom to explore its quieter, more surprising side - the Prague that reveals itself when you wander without a plan. Hidden courtyards, unexpected museums, small streets filled with stories: this is where the city feels most personal.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"563\" data-end=\"957\">You might choose to step into the <strong data-start=\"597\" data-end=\"618\">Museum of Alchemy</strong>, where myth, science, and medieval curiosity intertwine, or visit the <strong data-start=\"689\" data-end=\"711\">Franz Kafka Museum</strong>, an unusual and thought-provoking space that reflects the author&rsquo;s surreal inner world. A stop at the <strong data-start=\"814\" data-end=\"829\">Lennon Wall</strong> adds a different note - colorful, symbolic, and constantly evolving, it has stood as a message of peace and freedom since 1980.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"959\" data-end=\"1178\">The rest of the day is yours to shape. Browse local shops in search of a meaningful souvenir, enjoy a long lunch in a traditional restaurant, or simply wander - because in Prague, getting lost is part of the experience.<br><br></p>\r\n<h3 data-start=\"1185\" data-end=\"1244\"><strong data-start=\"1189\" data-end=\"1244\">Optional Experience &ndash; Kutn&aacute; Hora &amp; Konopi&scaron;tě Castle</strong></h3>\r\n<p data-start=\"1246\" data-end=\"1503\">For those curious to discover more of Bohemia beyond Prague, an optional excursion takes you to <strong data-start=\"1342\" data-end=\"1356\">Kutn&aacute; Hora</strong>, once one of the richest cities in medieval Europe thanks to its silver mines. In the 14th century, it rivaled even London in size and importance.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1505\" data-end=\"1783\">Here, you explore landmarks such as <strong data-start=\"1541\" data-end=\"1568\">St. Barbara&rsquo;s Cathedral</strong>, a masterpiece of Gothic architecture, the <strong data-start=\"1612\" data-end=\"1629\">Italian Court</strong> &mdash; home to the royal mint where Prague&rsquo;s famous silver coins were struck &mdash; and the historic streets that earned the city its UNESCO World Heritage status.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1785\" data-end=\"2095\">The journey continues to <strong data-start=\"1810\" data-end=\"1830\">Konopi&scaron;tě Castle</strong>, the former residence of Archduke Franz Ferdinand of Austria. Surrounded by forests and gardens, the castle offers a glimpse into aristocratic life at the turn of the 20th century, as well as a poignant reminder of the events that changed European history forever.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"2097\" data-end=\"2204\">In the late afternoon, you return to Prague, carrying with you a deeper understanding of the region&rsquo;s past.</p>\r\n<hr data-start=\"2206\" data-end=\"2209\">\r\n<p data-start=\"2211\" data-end=\"2379\">In the evening, you settle back into your hotel for another peaceful night.<br data-start=\"2286\" data-end=\"2289\"><strong data-start=\"2289\" data-end=\"2307\">Accommodation:</strong> Amedia Express Prague, Trademark Collection by Wyndham 3★ (or similar).</p>','Prague and Kutná Hora',NULL,'Optional Kutná Hora trip',NULL,3,'2025-12-19 16:35:43','2025-12-19 16:35:43'),(78,53,'Day 4 - last day - departure day',4,'<p>Prague - your home (arrival) airport</p>\r\n<p>Breakfast. You will leave behind the beautiful places you visited and will board the shuttle bus to the airport for the flight home.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,'2025-12-19 16:37:12','2025-12-19 16:37:12');
